General Notes About Vortex Messages: - Reported winds are usually averaged over a 10 second period. This temperature may not be the highest recorded on the inbound leg but is representative of the environmental temperature just outside the central region of the storm." - The maximum flight level temperature inside the eye (item J.) is the "maximum temperature observed within 5 nm of the center fix coordinates. If a higher temperature is observed at a location more than 5 nm away from the flight level center (item BRAVO), it is reported in Remarks, including bearing and distance from the flight level center."(Quotes from National Hurricane Operations Plan - NHOP)
